tions"},{"source":"recgAvM2HotRLjYjo","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recgAvM2HotRLjYjo","target":"recQ1bj3p4Lj5MYY6","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec3vZRWayjsbm6v8","ref":"Isa.33.1","text":"Woe to thee that spoilest, and thou wast not spoiled; and dealest treacherously, and they dealt not treacherously with thee! when thou shalt cease to spoil, thou shalt be spoiled; and when thou shalt make an end to deal treacherously, they shall deal treacherously with thee.","year":-713},{"id":"receEYqUtWjfMAeFb","ref":"Isa.33.2","text":"O LORD, be gracious unto us; we have waited for thee: be thou their arm every morning, our salvation also in the time of trouble.","year":-713},{"id":"recakmEQcx4atND6w","ref":"Isa.33.3","text":"At the noise of the tumult the people fled; at the lifting up of thyself the nations were scattered.","year":-713},{"id":"recHrjovEKURhsMbe","ref":"Isa.33.4","text":"And your spoil shall be gathered like the gathering of the caterpiller: as the running to and fro of locusts shall he run upon them.","year":-713},{"id":"recl0gLlnz6B2l4Bf","ref":"Isa.33.5","text":"The LORD is exalted; for he dwelleth on high: he hath filled Zion with judgment and righteousness.","year":-713},{"id":"recqWw5LArWQOokW4","ref":"Isa.33.6","text":"And wisdom and knowledge shall be the stability of thy times, and strength of salvation: the fear of the LORD is his treasure.","year":-713},{"id":"recgdwpKX3AiRPx7Y","ref":"Isa.33.7","text":"Behold, their valiant ones shall cry without: the ambassadors of peace shall weep bitterly.","year":-713},{"id":"recbxy7R2HkThN5MV","ref":"Isa.33.8","text":"The highways lie waste, the wayfaring man ceaseth: he hath broken the covenant, he hath despised the cities, he regardeth no man.","year":-713}]}
